      "targeted_response_start_logprob": 0.0
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Acknowledging the eventual end is a very honest observation of reality, and it can certainly feel bleak. However, focusing solely on the absolute finality can overshadow the intensity of what *is* happening right now. Even if all things are temporary, the experience of love, awe, or joy while they exist feels incredibly meaningful to the consciousness experiencing them. Perhaps shifting the focus from eternal meaning to the quality of the present moment can offer some respite.",
